          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do i use the front pockets?",
            "answer": "<p>The front pockets act as a chest fairing, filling the void between your chest and jersey to reduce air resistance. The more you fill them — with a bidon, gels, or a radio — the more aerodynamic advantage you gain, as a fuller pocket creates a smoother surface for air to flow over</p>",
